schema:creator: Hutchins, Wells A.
schema:description: This shows the type of slate rock used for the two outer walls of this fill. The only hydraulic material was placed inside. Owing to the looseness of this slate rock, the fill has settled several inches. At the bottom of the picture is shown the lower end of the storm culvert beneath the fill.
schema:name: Section of Morgan Fill, Turlock Irrigation District, Cal.
